{"lemma":"هَرْجِ","slug":"هَرْجِ","root":"ه.ر.ج","root_slug":"ه-ر-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ه-ر-ج","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":11},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n41116","n41120"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%87%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D8%AC%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be in disorder, to be in great confusion, to be in great commotion"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be agitated, to be confused, to be excited"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to handle or deal with clumsily"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mix up, to clutter"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make out with, to get busy with, to cohabit","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to leave open (a door)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to kill","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to agitate, to disrupt, to put into (more) commotion, to stir up, to get (someone) excited","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to jest, to play around (by being silly or the like), to clown around, to play the fool, to behave in a silly or foolish way","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of هَرَجَ (haraja) (form I), commotion, tumult","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"fatuous, sottish","tags":["obsolete"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n41116","headword_ar":"هَرِجَ","root":"hrj","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harojN","text_ar":"هَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did, acted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"occupied himself, much in a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"expatiated, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to a wide range,"},{"kind":"text","text":"in it. (L.) This is the original signification. (S,) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harj fiY","text_ar":"هَرج فِى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHidiyvi","text_ar":"الحِدِيثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (aor,"},{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harojN","text_ar":"هَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". Msb.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He launched into, and expatiated in."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was diffuse in discourse, talk"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"narration"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) this is the signification in most frequent use: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he made a confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"confounded, therein."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, Msb.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haraj","text_ar":"هَرَج"},{"kind":"text","text":". aor"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harojN","text_ar":"هَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Multum inivit"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. L.) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inivit"},{"kind":"text","text":"an cillam suam (K.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haraja","text_ar":"هَرَجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harojN","text_ar":"هَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a horse)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran much"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S. L:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran quickly"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"swiftly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or [simply]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ran"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"haraja Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"هَرَجَ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harojN","text_ar":"هَرْجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S.)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The people fell into a state of trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"civil war"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict and faction"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discussion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitonap","text_ar":"فِتْنَة"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disorder,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and slaughter."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harija","text_ar":"هَرِجَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"harajN","text_ar":"هَرَجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a camel)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became perplexed in his sight, by reason of the vehemence of heat, and his being much smeared with pitch,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and being heavily laden."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","K","TA","Msb"]},{"entry_id":"n41120","headword_ar":"هَرْجٌ","root":"hrj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"civil war,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict and faction,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"discord,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dissension."},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fitanopN","text_ar":"فِتَنْةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and confusion."},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disorder:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"vehement and much slaughter"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) in a trad. respecting the signs of the last day,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conflict, and confusion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disorder:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slaughter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as explained by Mohammad himself: (S:) and so, accord to Aboo-Moosa. It signifies in the language of Abyssinia (TA.) Ibn-Keys Fr-Rukeiyát said in the days of the faction of Ibn-Ez-Zubayi."},{"kind":"quote","text":"layot $iEoriY A^aA^aw~alu Alharoji h`*aA\n                      \n                     \n                        A^amN zamaAnN mino fitonapi gayori haroji"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Would that I knew whether this be the first of the slaughter predicted as a sign of the last day"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whether it be a time of trial,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"civil war"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other than the slaughter so predicted"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S)"}],"source_refs":["S","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}